Present location: INSTITUT DE PAPYROLOGIE ET D'ÉGYPTOLOGIE, UNIVERSITÉ DE LILLE III [02/049] LILLE
Name: Rectangular tablet
Description: Polished rectangular tablet pierced longitudinally. Both surfaces have been decorated with three rows of four circles. This motif is reminiscent of the impressions of seals identified by concentric circles, a coarse motif widespread during the Middle Kingdom and the Second Intermediate Period.
